rding-to-baristas-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStarbucks%20worker%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20North%20Carolina%20caf%C3%A9%20who%20has%20spent%2019%20years%20at%20the%20company%2C%20Schultz's%20decision%20on%20healthcare%20benefits%20symbolizes%20what%20Starbucks%20once%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20used%20to%20be%20a%20great%20place%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20wouldn't%20leave%20Starbucks%20unless%20they%20were%20college%20students%20and%20went%20up%20into%20a%20higher%20career%2C%20or%20they%20retired%20with%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%20The%20employee%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20in%20this%20article%2C%20citing%20fear%20of%20retaliation%20from%20Starbucks%2C%20but%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20identity%20and%20work%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20is%20at%20a%20crossroads.%20The%20company%20has%20spent%20several%20years%20fighting%20employees%20at%20hundreds%20of%20stores%20as%20they%20attempted%20to%20form%20unions%20and%20negotiate%20contracts%20%E2%80%94%20though%20Starbucks%20said%20this%20year%20that%20it%20would%20sit%20down%20to%20bargain%20with%20those%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20also%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20CEO%20change.%20Starbucks%20said%20last%20month%20that%20Chipotle%20CEO%20Brian%20Niccol%20would%20replace%20Laxman%20Narasimhan%20as%20CEO%20as%20of%20September%209.%20The%20switch%20comes%20as%20Starbucks%20faces%20slumping%20sales%20in%20the%20US%2C%20long%20customer%20wait%20times%2C%20and%20challenges%20in%20its%20business%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20continued%20healthcare%20option%20for%20part-time%20workers%2C%20the%20North%20Carolina%20employee%20pointed%20to%20the%20company's%20stock%20grant%20program%2C%20called%20Bean%20Stock%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20decision%20to%20call%20store%20employees%20%26quot%3Bpartners.%26quot%3B%20Starbucks%20began%20both%20in%201991%2C%20during%20Schultz's%20early%20years%20as%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20employee%2C%20who%20started%20working%20at%20Starbucks%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%2C%20said%20the%20company%20had%20a%20reputation%20for%20treating%20workers%20well%20when%20he%20joined.%20But%20changes%20over%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20such%20as%20cuts%20to%20staffing%20levels%20at%20his%20store%20and%20an%20increasing%20stream%20of%20mobile%20orders%2C%20have%20changed%20that%20image%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Starbucks%20location%20where%20the%20employee%20works%20now%20has%20two%20or%20three%20people%20on%20duty%20most%20shifts%2C%20down%20from%20up%20to%20five%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20said.%20That%20leaves%20partners%20more%20stretched%2C%20especially%20with%20a%20constant%20stream%20of%20orders%20placed%20through%20Starbucks'%20app%2C%20and%20less%20time%20to%20serve%20customers%20who%20order%20in-store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20started%20out%20as%20a%20trendy%2C%20quirky%20coffee%20shop%20job%2C%20and%20it's%20just%20morphed%20into%20this%20soulless%20fast%20food%20empire%20since%20that%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEver%20since%20Howard%20left%2C%20I%20said%20things%20have%20just%20really%20gone%20downhill%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20period%20after%20Schultz%20stepped%20down%20as%20CEO%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Starbucks%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20company%20seeks%20feedback%20from%20employees%20through%20surveys%20and%20meetings%20between%20employees%20and%20leadership.%20Store%20employees%20%26quot%3Bhave%20multiple%20opportunities%20throughout%20the%20year%20to%20voice%20their%20opinions%2C%20share%20their%20experiences%2C%20and%20suggest%20areas%20for%20improvement%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street%20analysts%20have%20lauded%20incoming%20CEO%20Niccol%20as%20the%20turnaround%20expert%20that%20Starbucks%20needs%2C%20citing%20Chipotle's%20severalfold%20stock%20p