quot%3B%20one%20former%20worker%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20spend%20eight%20hours%20a%20day%20for%20months%20on%20end%20just%20labeling%20lane%20lines%20and%20curbs%20across%20thousands%20of%20videos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22792b1597-e2f2-45b5-bc0f-f0c08f8864a3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20'intimate%20view%20into%20someone's%20life'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clips%20can%20provide%20a%20unique%20window%20into%20Tesla%20drivers'%20everyday%20lives.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20there%20was%20a%20project%20that%20required%20workers%20to%20label%20data%20taken%20from%20inside%20some%20owners'%20garages%20via%20Tesla's%20Sentry%20Mode%20feature%2C%20five%20workers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20project%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BSelfie%2C%26quot%3B%20required%20some%20annotators%20to%20label%20data%20taken%20from%20Tesla's%20in-cabin%20cameras%2C%20according%20to%20two%20workers%20who%20witnessed%20employees%20working%20on%20the%20project.%20Four%20additional%20workers%20said%20they%20were%20aware%20of%20the%20program.%20The%20Selfie%20program%20was%20designed%20to%20teach%20Tesla's%20system%20how%20to%20identify%20when%20a%20driver%20wasn't%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20road%20while%20Autopilot%20was%20in%20use%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20said%20that%20the%20vehicles'%20in-cabin%20camera%20%26quot%3Bshares%20short%20cabin%20camera%20video%20clips%20with%20Tesla%20to%20help%20us%20develop%20future%20safety%20enhancements%20and%20continuously%20improve%20the%20intelligence%20of%20features%20that%20rely%20on%20the%20cabin%20camera%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tesla.com%2Fownersmanual%2Fmodely%2Fen_us%2FGUID-EDAD116F-3C73-40FA-A861-68112FF7961F.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowner's%20manuals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Tesla%20owners%20must%20first%20opt-in%20to%20sharing%20their%20data%20for%20Tesla's%20labelers%20to%20be%20able%20to%20access%20the%20videos%2C%20the%20company%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20workers%20found%20themselves%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-prioritizes-musk-vip-data-self-driving-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabeling%20routes%20associated%20with%20YouTubers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20even%20Elon%20Musk%20himself%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20something%20very%20strange%20about%20having%20this%20very%20intimate%20view%20into%20someone's%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20current%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20odd%20to%20see%20someone's%20daily%20drive%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20an%20important%20part%20of%20correcting%20and%20refining%20the%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20videos%20are%20taken%20from%20across%20the%20US%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20regions%20in%20Europe%20and%20South%20America%2C%2015%20workers%20said.%20Two%20workers%20recalled%20labeling%20videos%20they%20believed%20had%20been%20taken%20from%20customer%20cars%20in%20Ukraine%20during%20Russia's%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20reached%20out%20to%20Tesla%2C%20Musk%2C%20and%20his%20legal%20team%20for%20comment%20but%20did%20not%20receive%20a%20response%20ahead%20of%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tesla%20autopilot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5b44f3df967ba5c8378b48d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETesla's%20driver-assist%20software%20can%20automatically%20change%20lanes%20and%20stop%20at%20traffic%20lights.%3Cp%3EMark%20Matousek%20%2F%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20can%20run%20into%20data%20from%20any%20number%20of%20countries%20in%20a%20single%20workflow%2C%20meaning%20they%20must%20constantly%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20different%20road%20rules%20for%20each%20region.%20At%20times%2C%20Tesla%20seemed%20to%20take%20a%20more%20relaxed%20stance%20on%20those%20rules%2C%20seven%20former%20and%20current%20workers%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20some%20workers%20said%20they%20were%20told%20to%20ignore%20%26quot%3BNo%20Turn%20on%20Red%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BNo%20U-Turn%26quot%3B%20signs%2C%20meaning%20they%20would%20not%20train%20the%20system%20to%20adhere%20to%20those%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20driver-first%20mentality%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20worker%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20idea%20is%20we%20want%20to%20train%20it%20to%20drive%20like%20a%20human%20would%2C%20not%20a%20robot%20that's%20just%20following%20the%20rules.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20the%20role%20requires%20workers%20to%20label%20videos%20from%20accidents%20and%20near-misses.%20Seven%20workers%20recalled%20labeling%20videos%20that%20included%20Tesla%20accidents%20or%20those%20involving%20nearby%20vehicles.%20At%20one%20point%20a%20worker%20even%20distributed%20a%20video%20between%20employees%20of%20an%20incident%20that%20involved%20a%20young%20boy%20on%20a%20bicycle%20getting%20hit%20by%20a%20Tesla%2C%20four%20workers%20said.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20many%20videos%20and%20memes%20workers%20used%20to%20exchange%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Reuters%20was%20the%20first%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftesla-workers-shared-sensitive-images-recorded-by-customer-cars-2023-04-06%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20bicycle%20clip%20and%20potential%20privacy%20issues%20at%20the%20annotation%20sites.%20Shortly%20after%20the%20article%20was%20published%2C%20Tesla%20began%20restricting%20access%20to%20clips%20outside%20of%20workers'%20designated%20projects%20and%20added%20watermarks%20to%20some%20of%20the%20videos%20and%20images%20so%20they%20could%20easily%20track%20down%20which%20employees%20were%20sharing%20images%2C%209%20workers%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d209187-0b66-4542-a27e-db8e6f98efdc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETesla's%20employee%20monitoring%20systems%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20fairly%20strict%20employee%20monitoring%20systems%20at%20its%20Buffalo%20site.%20The%20location%20has%20an%20array%20of%20surveillance%20cameras%20at%20the%20site%20that%20overlooks%20the%20workspace%2C%2011%20workers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20are%20also%20very%20closely%20monitored%20using%20two%20different%20software%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20system%2C%20called%20HuMans%2C%20gauges%20how%20long%20they%20should%20spend%20on%20each%20clip%2C%20four%20workers%20said.%20Annotators%20who%20take%20consistently%20longer%20than%20the%20allotted%20time%20are%20likely%20to%20receive%20poor%20performance%20reviews%20or%20be%20put%20under%20a%20performance%20improvement%20plan%2C%20or%20PIP%2C%20they%20said.%20The%20software%20was%20originally%20designed%20to%20help%20pilots%20in%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20and%20also%20has%20the%20capability%20of%20tracking%20employees'%20eye%20movement%20and%20taking%20audio%20recordings%2C%20according%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thalesgroup.com%2Fen%2Fhumans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it's%20unclear%20if%20Tesla%20uses%20the%20software%20to%20track%20staff's%20eye%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20uses%20a%20measure%20called%20%26quot%3BFlide%20Time%26quot%3B%20to%20track%20annotators'%20active%20time%20on%20the%20labeling%20software%2C%2017%20workers%20said.%20It%20can%20track%20keystrokes%20and%20how%20long%20workers%20spend%20with%20the%20labeling%20software%20open%2C%20but%20it%20won't%20track%20the%20time%20workers%20spend%20using%20other%20tools%20on%20their%20computer%2C%20they%20said.%20Depending%20on%20their%20level%2C%20workers%20can%20be%20expected%20to%20log%20anywhere%20from%20five%20to%20seven%20and%20a%20half%20hours%20of%20Flide%20Time%2C%20meaning%20they%20must%20be%20active%20on%20the%20software%20for%20at%20least%20that%20amount%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20workers%20are%20even%20five%20minutes%20short%20of%20hitting%20their%20designated%20Flide%20Time%20they%20could%20face%20disciplinary%20action%2C%20six%20workers%20said.%20If%20they%20miss%20Flide%20Time%20three%20times%20in%20the%20span%20of%20six%20months%2C%20they%20could%20be%20terminated%2C%20the%20workers%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Tesla%20workers%20have%20attempted%20to%20push%20back%20on%20the%20company's%20metrics%20for%20staff%20with%20little%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20some%20workers%20at%20Tesla's%20Buffalo%20facility%20attempted%20to%20unionize.%20Union%20organizers%20at%20the%20Buffalo%20facility%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-02-14%2Ftesla-autopilot-workers-launch-union-campaign-in-buffalo-new-york-tsla%3Fsref%3DLspfQlRv%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20was%20tracking%20their%20keystrokes%20and%20said%20some%20workers%20had%20grown%20weary%20of%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20treated%20like%20robots.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20month%20Tesla%20laid%20off%20dozens%20of%20workers%20at%20the%20Buffalo%20plant.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20The%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%20(NLRB)%20filed%20a%20complaint%20alleging%20that%20Tesla%20unlawfully%20terminated%20some%20staff%20%26quot%3Bin%20retaliation%20for%20union%20activity%20and%20to%20discourage%20union%20activity.%26quot%3B%20But%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-laid-off-new-york-workers-poor-performance-union-campaign-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETesla%20denied%20the%20allegation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20employees%20were%20laid%20off%20due%20to%20poor%20performance%20instead.%20The%20NLRB%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20the%20current%20status%20of%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Tesla%20began%20building%20its%20driver%20assist%20program%20in%202016%20the%20company%20outsourced%20data%20labeling%20to%20a%20California-based%20company%20that%20had%20offices%20in%20Kenya%2C%20but%20Tesla%20brought%20the%20program%20in-house%20in%202019%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20Tesla's%20Autopilot%20team%20was%20hit%20by%20companywide%20layoffs%20in%20April.%20Tesla%20shed%20nearly%20300%20of%20its%20staff%20in%20Buffalo%2C%20according%20to%20a%20WARN%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20said%20its%20neural%20network%20will%20someday%20be%20able%20to%20train%20itself%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20it%20relies%20on%20its%20human%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20work%20is%20vital%20to%20Musk's%20vision%20for%20the%20car%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20Tesla%20CEO%20has%20repeatedly%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20Tesla's%20efforts%20toward%20achieving%20autonomous%20driving.%20In%202022%2C%20Musk%20said%20Tesla's%20self-driving%20technology%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bdifference%20between%20Tesla%20being%20worth%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20or%20worth%20basically%20zero.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20plans%20to%20unveil%20its%20autonomous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-says-tesla-robotaxi-event-delay-due-to-redesign-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobotaxi%20service%20later%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20built%20upon%20that%20same%20self-driving%20software%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20tedious%2C%20clip-by-clip%20analysis%20of%20its%20labelers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Tesla%20or%20have%20a%20tip%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporter%20via%20a%20non-work%20email%20and%20device%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Agkay%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Egkay%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%2