i%3EAn%20air%20traffic%20controller%20in%20Australia%20was%20found%20asleep%20under%20a%20blanket%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20shift.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20had%20worked%20seven%20night%20shifts%20in%20nine%20days%20due%20to%20staffing%20changes%2C%20a%20safety%20investigation%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20report%20said%20an%20%26quot%3Bunderlying%20lack%20of%20resources%26quot%3B%20contributed%20to%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20air%20traffic%20controller%20at%20a%20major%20Australian%20airport%20was%20found%20asleep%20at%20the%20end%20of%20their%20night%20shift%2C%20according%20to%20an%20investigation%20by%20the%20Australian%20Transport%20Safety%20Bureau%20(ATSB).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worker%20had%20signed%20on%20for%20their%20night%20shift%2C%20which%20ran%20from%2010%20p.m.%20to%206%20a.m.%2C%20at%20the%20Brisbane%20Centre%2C%20a%20major%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecoming-air-traffic-controller-career-pros-cons-of-job-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eair%20traffic%20control%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Brisbane%20Airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrisbane%20is%20Australia's%20third-busiest%20airport%2C%20handling%20around%2022.6%20million%20passengers%20annually.%20It%20has%20consistently%20been%20among%20the%20100%20busiest%20airports%20in%20the%20world%20and%20was%20ranked%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldairportawards.com%2Fworlds-top-100-airports-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20the%20world's%2032nd-best%20by%20Skytrax%20in%202024%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%209%2C%202022%2C%20the%20morning%20shift%20controller%20arrived%20at%20work%20at%205%3A15%20a.m.%20to%20find%20their%20night%20shift%20counterpart%20asleep%20at%20the%20console.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worker%20was%20discovered%20lying%20across%20two%20chairs%20with%20a%20blanket%20covering%20them%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atsb.gov.au%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-09%2FAO-2022-065%2520%2528Final%2529.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20were%20still%20wearing%20their%20headset%2C%20and%20the%20air%20situation%20display%20(ASD)%20screensaver%20was%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20ensuring%20there%20was%20no%20traffic%20in%20the%20area%2C%20the%20station%20was%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20oncoming%20controller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20controller%20was%20monitoring%20air%20traffic%20in%20and%20around%20Cairns%2C%20a%20city%20around%20850%20miles%20north%20of%20Brisbane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20the%20Brisbane%20Centre%20building%20was%20cooler%20at%20night%2C%20and%20it%20was%20considered%20normal%20practice%20for%20blankets%20to%20be%20used%20during%20night%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ATSB's%20report%20blamed%20multiple%20night%20shifts%20in%20a%20short%20space%20of%20time%2C%20the%20worker's%20low%20workload%2C%20and%20an%20ineffective%20risk%20management%20system%20for%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20the%20worker%20had%2010%20years%20of%20experience%20as%20a%20controller%20and%20had%20been%20in%20their%20current%20position%20for%20three%20years.%20However%2C%20due%20to%20last%20minute%20roster%20changes%2C%20they%20had%20worked%20their%20seventh%20night%20shift%20in%20nine%20days%20and%20had%20not%20taken%20the%20recommended%20rest%20period%20in%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%20Brisbane%20Centre%20air%20traffic%20controller%20who%20was%20found%20asleep%20at%20their%20workstation%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20their%20shift%20had%20worked%20multiple%20consecutive%20night%20shifts%20resulting%20in%20sleep%20debt%2C%20an%20ATSB%20investigation%20report%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20ATSB%20(%40atsbgovau)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fatsbgovau%2Fstatus%2F1830791268907278639%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%203%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20had%20been%20no%20traffic%20or%20scheduled%20flights%20in%20the%20airspace%20the%20controller%20was%20responsible%20for%20and%20a%20system%20supervisor%20had%20been%20on%20duty%20at%20the%20front%20desk%20of%20the%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20cumulative%20fatigue%20was%20not%20being%20effectively%20managed%20at%20the%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLikely%20due%20to%20an%20underlying%20lack%20of%20resources%20within%20Airservices%20Australia%2C%20there%20was%20an%20over-reliance%20on%20tactical%20changes%20to%20manage%20the%20roster%2C%26quot%3B%20investigators%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ATSB%20said%20it%20would%20update%20its%20safety%20procedures%20and%20fatigue%20risk%20management%20regulations%20in%20response%20to%20the%20incident%2C%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20monitor%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirservices%20Australia%2C%20which%20runs%20the%20Brisbane%20Centre%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it%20has%20%26quot%3Breviewed%20and%20updated%20guidance%20to%20our%20staff%20on%20fatigue%20management%20processes%2C%20and%20is%20working%20with%20CASA%20to%20explore%20further%20improvements%20on%20our%20fatigue%20risk%20management%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20fatigue%20has%20been%20a%20growing%20safety%20concern%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairport-collision-close-call-solutions-sleep-runways-air-traffic-controllers-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshortages%20of%20air%20traffic%20controllers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20driven%20up%20the%20amount%20of%20overtime%20required%20for%20those%20that%20remain.%20Some%20controllers%20have%20turned%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22