ref%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-dinks-winning-childfree-economy-finances-income-vacation-retirement-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20time%20and%20expendable%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20focus%20on%20other%20endeavors%2C%20such%20as%20travel%20and%20social%20outings.%20In%20one%20year%2C%20they%20went%20to%20Greece%20and%20Hawaii%2C%20plus%20a%20host%20of%20local%20concerts%20and%20comedy%20shows.%20Gonzalez%2C%2028%2C%20also%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20her%20flexibility%20as%20a%20DINK%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20her%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-dink-quit-job-glory-days-over2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epivot%20her%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20opting%20out%20of%20kids%20came%20with%20a%20downside%3A%20being%20the%20last%20of%20their%20college%20friend%20group%20to%20be%20child-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20surreal%20to%20see%20myself%20surrounded%20by%20my%20friends%20who%20are%20all%20having%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGonzalez%2C%20based%20in%20Virginia%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20affected%20our%20friendship%20in%20terms%20of%20we%20don't%20hang%20out%20with%20them%20as%20much.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchild-free-lonely-so-we-started-walking-group-for-women-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echild-free%20couples%20report%20feeling%20lonelier%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20most%20or%20all%20of%20their%20friends%20start%20families.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Ftherealmrbench%2Fstatus%2F1732102826304864452%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOnline%20commenters%20warn%20against%20DINK%20lifestyles%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20that%20opting%20out%20of%20kids%20also%20means%20opting%20out%20of%20the%20communities%20formed%20%3Cem%3Earound%3C%2Fem%3E%20kids%2C%20such%20as%20friendships%20with%20other%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20contrary%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FCannibalSlang%2Fstatus%2F1732266659644141808%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estereotypes%20of%20DINKs%3C%2Fa%3E%20growing%20old%20alone%2C%20many%20are%20using%20their%2030s%20to%20forge%20the%20deepest%20connections%20of%20their%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20from%20becoming%20aunties%20to%20their%20friends'%20children%20to%20forming%20relationships%20in%20the%20unlikeliest%20of%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22428e05e6-6785-4202-b931-a41bb1946941%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMillennial%20DINKs%20might%20not%20know%20where%20they%20fit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20households%20have%20changed%20dramatically%20since%20boomers%20were%20parents.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusafacts.org%2Farticles%2Fhow-has-the-structure-of-american-households-changed-over-time%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%201960%2C%20married%20parents%20made%20up%2044%25%20of%20all%20US%20households%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202022%2C%20they%20were%20outnumbered%20by%20both%20single%20people%20and%20child-free%20couples%20%E2%80%94%20that%20year%2C%20there%20were%2038.1%20million%20married%20and%20childless%20households%2C%20a%20140%25%20increase%20over%201960%2C%20according%20to%20USA%20Facts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20millennials%20are%20marrying%20later%20than%20past%20generations%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrjesscarbino.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Jess%20Carbino%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20sociologist%20for%20Tinder%20and%20Bumble%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20If%20boomers%20followed%20more%20of%20a%20uniform%20timeline%20%E2%80%94%20get%20married%20and%20have%20kids%20in%20your%2020s%20%E2%80%94%20millennials%20are%20hitting%20those%20milestones%20at%20different%20ages%2C%20or%20not%20at%20all.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20this%20in-between%20period%20for%20these%20individuals%20who%20are%20choosing%20to%20be%20childless%2C%26quot%3B%20Carbino%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandra%20Kushnir%2C%2032%2C%20grew%20up%20in%20Utah%2C%20where%20her%20closest%20childhood%20friends%20now%20have%20families.%20The%20difference%20in%20lifestyles%20and%20schedules%20makes%20it%20hard%20to%20plan%20activities%20she'd%20love%20to%20do%20with%20them%2C%20such%20as%20group%20vacations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20moved%20to%20LA%20with%20her%20husband%20to%20focus%20on%20their%20careers%20and%20find%20friends%20with%20similar%20lifestyles.%20But%20while%20they%20have%20plenty%20of%20childless%20single%20and%20coupled%20friends%2C%20that%20doesn't%20always%20translate%20to%20understanding%2C%20either.%20Some%20are%20%26quot%3Bstill%20doing%20drugs%20and%20drinking%20and%20going%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Kushnir%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20that%20anymore%2C%20but%20we%20also%20don't%20have%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c52e2fce-c22d-4b30-ae79-1c5d59713f28%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20creative%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20parent%20friends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it's%20hard%20to%20be%20as%20spontaneous%20with%20friends%20who%20have%20kids%2C%20DINK%20couples%20have%20to%20make%20some%20adjustments.%20Gonzalez%20and%20her%20husband%20travel%20to%20their%20friends'%20homes%20a%20few%20times%20a%20year%20instead%20of%20meeting%20halfway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Alexander%2C%2035%2C%20said%20she%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20travel%20with%20friends'%20kids%2C%20such%20as%20an%20upcoming%20trip%20to%20Disney%20Paris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20with%20kids%20can't%20just%20go%20do%20something%20at%20the%20last%20minute%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Seattle%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20probably%20the%20biggest%20thing%20we've%20had%20to%20shift%2C%20is%20finding%20friends%20who%20have%20more%20availability%20to%20maybe%20just%20drop%20things%20and%20go%20do%20something.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20tell%20people%2C%20'I%20still%20want%20to%20be%20in%20your%20life%2C'%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20added.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20I%20do%20think%20that%20there's%20this%20idea%20that%20once%20you%20have%20kids%2C%20you%20can't%20find%20any%20overlap.%20And%20I%20don't%20really%20think%20that's%20true.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJess%20Lorimer%2C%20based%20in%20Southhampton%2C%20UK%2C%20said%20there%20are%20pluses%20to%20being%20the%20child-free%20friends%2C%20such%20as%20having%20disposable%20income%20and%20additional%20energy.%20Childless%20people%20like%20her%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20the%20fun%20auntie%20uncle%20energy%20that%20you%20might%20not%20always%20be%20able%20to%20be%20as%20the%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20Lorimer%2C%2033%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20She%20enjoys%20going%20on%20trips%20with%20her%20parent%20friends%20and%20helping%20their%20kids%20build%20sandcastles%20or%20bringing%20back%20gifts%20from%20vacations%20for%20the%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292e844b2-d178-41db-9468-cb1c10a97da8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20new%20friends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20old%20friends%20being%20busy%20with%20kids%20can%20leave%20social%20gaps%20for%20DINKs%20that%20aren't%20always%20easy%20to%20fill.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchris-duffy-making-friends-as-an-adult-can-be-hard-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaking%20friends%20in%20one's%2030s%3C%2Fa%3E%20comes%20with%20unique%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20gets%20busier%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20more%20responsibilities%2C%20it's%20much%20harder%20to%20keep%20the%20same%20level%20of%20friendship%20where%20you're%20seeing%20each%20other%20multiple%20times%20a%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbino%20said%20that%20DINKs%20have%20to%20look%20for%20groups%20or%20organizations%20where%20people%20are%20roughly%20the%20same%20age%20(or%20in%20the%20same%20life%20stage)%2C%20share%20the%20same%20general%20interests%2C%20and%20are%20also%20open%20and%20available%20for%20new%20friends%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20gets%20tougher%20as%20people%20get%20older%2C%20settle%20into%20their%20schedules%2C%20and%20stick%20to%20their%20core%20friend%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKushnir%20and%20her%20husband%20met%20some%20couple%20friends%20through%20Honeymoon%20Israel%2C%20a%2010-day%20trip%20that%20she%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bbirthright%26quot%3B%20for%20Jewish%20and%20interfaith%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20criteria%20where%20you%20have%20to%20be%202-5%20years%20into%20your%20relationship%2C%20engaged%20or%20married%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20kind%20of%20try%20to%20match%20couples%20that%20are%20in%20the%20same%20life%20stage%20as%20you%20on%20the%20trip.%26quot%3B%20They%20met%20multiple%20people%20just%20like%20them%3A%20interfaith%20couples%20with%20no%20kids%20(four%20of%20those%20couples%20went%20on%20to%20have%20kids%20around%20the%20same%20time).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKushnir%20said%20they%20also%20made%20like-minded%20friends%20by%20continuing%20to%20show%20up%20to%20a%20local%20dog%20park.%20They%20befriended%20other%20child-free%20couples%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-dinkwad-double-income-no-kids-dog-tiktok-trend-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDINKWADs%3C%2Fa%3E%20(DINKs%20With%20a%20Dog)%2C%20people%20who%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20share%20some%20of%20the%20same%20priorities%20and%20routines%20as%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221179%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20on%20the%20beach%20with%20their%20dog%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d213ec43b5e59d16b730da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221534%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESandra%20Kushnir%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20their%20dog.%3Cp%3ESandra%20Kushnir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20DINKs%20have%20had%20to%